

    1. Create docker images of your frontend and backend app
    2. Push them on Dockerhub
    3. Create 1 Deployment with 1 replica and 1 pod of your frontend application
    4. Create 1 Deployment with 1 replica and 1 pod of your backend application
    5. Add two NodePort services to verify your frontend and backend application is running
    6. Create a ClusterIp service for your backend service
    7. Enable the communication of your frontend with backend using above ClusterIP
    8. Verify whole application is running
    9. Scale your application with 3 replicas


